 for stadium construction, saddled taxpayers with huge cost overruns, and served as propaganda showcases for brutal authoritarian regimes, such as those of Russia, China, and Nazi Germany.\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 731, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 699, \"end\": 705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999986973988897, \"rank\": 1.3009916643531847e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 707, \"end\": 712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9997194176902772, \"rank\": 0.0002614897081902422, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 718, \"end\": 730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.5887923413963707, \"rank\": 0.6981760274864355, \"text\": \"Nazi Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Past games\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 474}, {\"ngram\": \"featuredhorrible forcible displacement\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"residents\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 531}, {\"ngram\": \"way\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 543}, {\"ngram\": \"stadium construction\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 568}, {\"ngram\": \"taxpayers\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 587}, {\"ngram\": \"huge cost overruns\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 611}, {\"ngram\": \"propaganda showcases\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 647}, {\"ngram\": \"brutal authoritarian regimes\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 680}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year's games are less bad than many previous ones.\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 788, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This year's games\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 750}, {\"ngram\": \"many previous ones\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 787}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France, for all its faults, is not a mass-murdering authoritarian state, like Russia or China.\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.99990575964541, \"rank\": 7.496952093002178e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 867, \"end\": 873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999986973988897, \"rank\": 1.3009916643531847e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9997194176902772, \"rank\": 0.0002614897081902422, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all its faults\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 815}, {\"ngram\": \"a mass-murdering authoritarian state\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 860}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the Paris organizers have, to some extent,kept costs down by relying on existing facilities.\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 892, \"end\": 897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999852730072, \"rank\": 1.472692451699355e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some extent\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 929}, {\"ngram\": \"costs\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 940}, {\"ngram\": \"existing facilities\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nonetheless, some migrants and homeless peoplehave been forcibly displaced for the games(researchersestimate that some 12,500 people were forced out), and I will be very surprised if French taxpayers avoid being burdened with severe cost overruns, even if they are smaller than those for many previous Olympics.\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1165, \"end\": 1171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9774744943126837, \"rank\": 0.022877263735153256, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some migrants\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1007}, {\"ngram\": \"homeless peoplehave\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1031}, {\"ngram\": \"the games(researchersestimate\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1089}, {\"ngram\": \"some 12,500 people\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1113}, {\"ngram\": \"severe cost overruns\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1227}, {\"ngram\": \"many previous Olympics\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1291}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It does not have to be that way.\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1327, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that way\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1326}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022, in the aftermath of the awful Beijing Winter Games, Ioutlined a series of reformsthat can fix the dark side of the Olympics, while preserving their role as a great athletic competition: 1.\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1526, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the aftermath\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1353}, {\"ngram\": \"the awful Beijing Winter Games\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1387}, {\"ngram\": \"a series\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"reformsthat\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1422}, {\"ngram\": \"the dark side\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1444}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1460}, {\"ngram\": \"their role\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1489}, {\"ngram\": \"a great athletic competition\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1521}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No public subsidies.\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1547, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No public subsidies\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1546}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let the games be funded purely by private organizations and sponsors, as was largely the casefor the successful 1984 Olympics in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1689, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1677, \"end\": 1688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999899956, \"rank\": 9.742193668801712e-12, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1561}, {\"ngram\": \"private organizations\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1603}, {\"ngram\": \"sponsors\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1616}, {\"ngram\": \"the casefor\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1644}, {\"ngram\": \"the successful 1984 Olympics\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1673}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That way, no one has to pay for the games, except those who profit from them and the audience that voluntarily chooses to watch.\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1818, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1706}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 1722, \"to\": 1731}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2.\", \"from\": 1820, \"to\": 1822, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No forcible displacement of residents, private businesses, or civil society organizations.\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1916, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No forcible displacement\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1847}, {\"ngram\": \"residents\", \"from\": 1851, \"to\": 1860}, {\"ngram\": \"private businesses\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1880}, {\"ngram\": \"civil society organizations\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1912}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We can and should hold sports events without kicking innocent people out of their homes.\", \"from\": 1917, \"to\": 2005, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports events\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 1953}, {\"ngram\": \"innocent people\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1985}, {\"ngram\": \"their homes\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 2004}]}, {\"sentence\": \"3.\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2009, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No hosting rights for authoritarian human rights violators.\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2069, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No hosting rights\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2027}, {\"ngram\": \"authoritarian human rights violators\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2068}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are plenty of possible Olympic venues that are not controlled by likes of Vladimir Putin and Xi Jinping.\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2150, \"end\": 2164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.309358922062876e-21, \"text\": \"Vladimir Putin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}, {\"begin\": 2169, \"end\": 2179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xi_Jinping\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Xi Jinping\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xi_Jinping\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xi_Jinping\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"plenty\", \"from\": 2080, \"to\": 2086}, {\"ngram\": \"possible Olympic venues\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2113}, {\"ngram\": \"likes\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2146}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Denying these types of rulers hosting rights will not fundamentally alter their regimes.\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2269, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these types\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2200}, {\"ngram\": \"rulers\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2210}, {\"ngram\": \"rights\", \"from\": 2219, \"to\": 2225}, {\"ngram\": \"their regimes\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2268}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it will at least damage their image and deny them propaganda victories.\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2345, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their image\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2309}, {\"ngram\": \"propaganda victories\", \"from\": 2324, \"to\": 2344}]}, {\"sentence\": \"4.\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2349, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There must be full freedom of speech in the Olympic Village and all other Olympic venues.\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2394, \"end\": 2409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.137003978440915e-29, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"full freedom\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2376}, {\"ngram\": \"speech\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2386}, {\"ngram\": \"all other Olympic venues\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2438}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the very least, athletes, journalists, and spectators should be entirely free to criticize the host government and its policies (or any other government for that matter) [freedom of speech has often been violated when authoritarian states host the Games].\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2698, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \", athletes\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2467}, {\"ngram\": \"journalists\", \"from\": 2469, \"to\": 2480}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2496}, {\"ngram\": \"the host government\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2553}, {\"ngram\": \"its policies\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2570}, {\"ngram\": \"any other government\", \"from\": 